From December 8, 2020, the target area has been expanded. All arrivals who have been to the following areas within the past 14 days prior to their entry into Macau must undergo 14 days of medical observation at designated places in accordance with the requirements of the health authorities: 
1. Shanghai: Zhuqiao Town, Zhoupu Town, Zhangjiang Town of Pudong New District; 
2. Tianjin: the cold chain logistics area of the central fishing port, Hangu Street, or Dongjiang Port Area of Binhai New District; 
3. Inner Mongolia: Manzhouli or Zhalainuo’er District of Hulunbuir; 
4. Sichuan: Pitong Town (Pitong Street) in Pidu District, Chengdu. UPDATE: The geographical target of the policy has changed. Tangchang Town and Tiaodenghe Street (Sichuan, China) became additional targets since December 9.

